00:17:09.924 --> 00:17:12.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
“On the first day of the Unleavened Bread,

00:17:12.594 --> 00:17:15.388 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the disciples came to Jesus, saying:

00:17:16.139 --> 00:17:17.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Where do you want us to prepare for you

00:17:17.765 --> 00:17:19.392 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to eat the Passover?’

00:17:19.726 --> 00:17:20.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He said:

00:17:21.436 --> 00:17:23.730 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Go into the city to So-and-so

00:17:23.730 --> 00:17:26.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘and say to him, “The Teacher says:

00:17:26.774 --> 00:17:29.152 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“‘My appointed time is near;

00:17:29.152 --> 00:17:31.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“‘I will celebrate the Passover

00:17:31.154 --> 00:17:33.239 line:90% position:50% align:center
“with my disciples at your home.’”’

00:17:34.324 --> 00:17:36.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So the disciples did as Jesus instructed them

00:17:36.993 --> 00:17:39.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
and prepared for the Passover.”

00:17:48.588 --> 00:17:51.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The day of the Unleavened Bread now arrived,

00:17:51.466 --> 00:17:55.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
“on which the Passover sacrifice must be offered;

00:17:55.136 --> 00:17:59.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so Jesus sent Peter and John, saying:

00:17:59.265 --> 00:18:02.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Go and get the Passover ready for us to eat.’

00:18:02.977 --> 00:18:04.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
“They said to him:

00:18:04.687 --> 00:18:07.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Where do you want us to get it ready?’

00:18:07.190 --> 00:18:08.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He said to them:

00:18:08.691 --> 00:18:11.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Look! When you enter into the city,

00:18:11.778 --> 00:18:14.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘a man carrying an earthenware water jar

00:18:14.447 --> 00:18:15.865 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘will meet you.

00:18:15.865 --> 00:18:18.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Follow him into the house that he enters.

00:18:18.284 --> 00:18:20.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘And say to the landlord of the house,

00:18:20.787 --> 00:18:22.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“The Teacher says to you:

00:18:22.789 --> 00:18:24.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘“‘Where is the guest room

00:18:24.791 --> 00:18:27.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘where I may eat the Passover with my disciples?’”

00:18:28.461 --> 00:18:30.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘And that man will show you

00:18:30.463 --> 00:18:32.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘a large, furnished upper room.

00:18:32.840 --> 00:18:34.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Get it ready there.’

00:18:35.385 --> 00:18:39.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So they left and found it just as he had told them,

00:18:39.263 --> 00:18:41.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they prepared for the Passover.”

00:18:52.068 --> 00:18:53.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
“When evening came,

00:18:53.277 --> 00:18:56.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he was reclining at the table with the 12 disciples.

00:18:56.990 --> 00:18:59.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
“While they were eating, he said:

00:18:59.617 --> 00:19:04.122 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Truly I say to you, one of you will betray me.’ 

00:19:04.872 --> 00:19:08.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Being very much grieved at this,

00:19:08.251 --> 00:19:11.087 line:90% position:50% align:center
“each and every one began to say to him:

00:19:11.087 --> 00:19:15.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Lord, it is not I, is it?’

00:19:15.633 --> 00:19:17.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
“In reply he said:

00:19:17.927 --> 00:19:21.347 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘The one who dips his hand with me into the bowl

00:19:21.347 --> 00:19:24.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘is the one who will betray me.

00:19:24.058 --> 00:19:27.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘True, the Son of man is going away,

00:19:27.520 --> 00:19:29.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘just as it is written about him,

00:19:29.772 --> 00:19:31.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘but woe to that man

00:19:31.774 --> 00:19:34.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘through whom the Son of man is betrayed!

00:19:34.819 --> 00:19:37.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘It would have been better for that man

00:19:37.071 --> 00:19:39.490 line:90% position:50% align:center
if he had not been born.’

00:19:40.199 --> 00:19:45.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Judas, who was about to betray him, replied:

00:19:45.121 --> 00:19:48.291 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘It is not I, is it, Rabbi?’

00:19:49.000 --> 00:19:51.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jesus said to him:

00:19:51.002 --> 00:19:53.254 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘You yourself said it.’

00:19:57.133 --> 00:20:00.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
“As they continued eating, Jesus took a loaf,

00:20:00.720 --> 00:20:03.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and after saying a blessing, he broke it,

00:20:03.890 --> 00:20:06.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and giving it to the disciples, he said:

00:20:06.726 --> 00:20:11.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Take, eat. This means my body.’

00:20:12.690 --> 00:20:14.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And taking a cup, he offered thanks

00:20:14.984 --> 00:20:17.320 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and gave it to them, saying:

00:20:17.320 --> 00:20:19.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Drink out of it, all of you,

00:20:19.781 --> 00:20:22.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘for this means my “blood of the covenant,”

00:20:23.242 --> 00:20:25.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘which is to be poured out in behalf of many

00:20:25.495 --> 00:20:27.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘for forgiveness of sins.

00:20:27.663 --> 00:20:29.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘But I say to you:

00:20:29.665 --> 00:20:31.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘I will by no means drink again

00:20:31.709 --> 00:20:33.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘any of this product of the vine

00:20:33.753 --> 00:20:36.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘until that day when I drink it new with you

00:20:36.923 --> 00:20:38.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the Kingdom of my Father.’

00:20:42.178 --> 00:20:44.931 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Finally, after singing praises,

00:20:44.931 --> 00:20:47.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
“they went out to the Mount of Olives.

00:20:50.478 --> 00:20:52.814 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then Jesus said to them:

00:20:52.814 --> 00:20:54.816 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘All of you will be stumbled

00:20:54.816 --> 00:20:57.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘in connection with me on this night,

00:20:57.318 --> 00:21:00.822 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘for it is written: “I will strike the shepherd,

00:21:00.822 --> 00:21:04.367 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘and the sheep of the flock will be scattered about.”

00:21:04.367 --> 00:21:06.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘But after I have been raised up,

00:21:06.744 --> 00:21:09.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I will go ahead of you into Galilee.’

00:21:09.413 --> 00:21:13.292 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But Peter, in response, said to him:

00:21:13.292 --> 00:21:15.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Although all the others

00:21:15.002 --> 00:21:17.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘are stumbled in connection with you,

00:21:17.046 --> 00:21:19.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I will never be stumbled!’

00:21:19.549 --> 00:21:21.717 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jesus said to him:

00:21:21.717 --> 00:21:23.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Truly I say to you, 

00:21:23.845 --> 00:21:27.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘on this night, before a rooster crows,

00:21:27.723 --> 00:21:31.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
“you will disown me three times.’

00:21:31.894 --> 00:21:33.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Peter said to him:

00:21:33.896 --> 00:21:37.108 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Even if I should have to die with you,

00:21:37.108 --> 00:21:39.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I will by no means disown you.’

00:21:40.528 --> 00:21:43.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
“All the other disciples also said the same thing.

00:21:46.659 --> 00:21:48.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then Jesus came with them

00:21:48.452 --> 00:21:50.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to the spot called Gethsemane,

00:21:52.790 --> 00:21:54.876 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and he said to the disciples:

00:21:54.876 --> 00:21:59.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Sit down here while I go over there and pray.’

00:22:01.174 --> 00:22:02.717 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And taking along Peter

00:22:02.717 --> 00:22:04.760 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and the two sons of Zebʹe·dee,

00:22:04.760 --> 00:22:06.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he began to feel grieved

00:22:06.804 --> 00:22:08.931 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and to be greatly troubled.

00:22:08.931 --> 00:22:10.933 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then he said to them:

00:22:10.933 --> 00:22:15.813 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘I am deeply grieved, even to death.

00:22:15.813 --> 00:22:19.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Stay here and keep on the watch with me.’

00:22:19.942 --> 00:22:21.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And going a little way forward,

00:22:21.944 --> 00:22:25.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he fell facedown, praying:

00:22:25.573 --> 00:22:28.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘My Father, if it is possible,

00:22:28.993 --> 00:22:32.580 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘let this cup pass away from me.

00:22:32.580 --> 00:22:36.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Yet, not as I will, but as you will.’

00:22:38.169 --> 00:22:40.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He returned to the disciples

00:22:40.171 --> 00:22:42.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and found them sleeping,

00:22:42.256 --> 00:22:44.342 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and he said to Peter:

00:22:44.342 --> 00:22:47.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Could you not so much as keep on the watch

00:22:47.720 --> 00:22:49.931 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘for one hour with me?

00:22:49.931 --> 00:22:54.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Keep on the watch and pray continually,

00:22:54.185 --> 00:22:57.897 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘so that you may not enter into temptation.

00:22:57.897 --> 00:23:00.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘The spirit, of course, is eager,

00:23:00.566 --> 00:23:02.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but the flesh is weak.’

00:23:04.487 --> 00:23:08.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Again, a second time, he went off and prayed:

00:23:08.783 --> 00:23:10.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘My Father,

00:23:10.785 --> 00:23:14.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘if it is not possible for this to pass away

00:23:14.038 --> 00:23:16.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘unless I drink it,

00:23:16.040 --> 00:23:18.376 line:90% position:50% align:center
“let your will take place.’

00:23:19.001 --> 00:23:22.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And he came again and found them sleeping,

00:23:22.964 --> 00:23:25.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for their eyes were heavy.

00:23:26.759 --> 00:23:28.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So leaving them,

00:23:28.844 --> 00:23:31.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he again went off and prayed for a third time,

00:23:31.973 --> 00:23:34.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
“saying once more the same thing.

00:23:37.687 --> 00:23:41.023 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then he returned to the disciples and said to them: 

00:23:41.023 --> 00:23:43.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘At such a time as this,

00:23:43.150 --> 00:23:45.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘you are sleeping and resting!

00:23:46.779 --> 00:23:49.490 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Look! The hour has drawn near

00:23:49.490 --> 00:23:51.867 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘for the Son of man to be betrayed

00:23:51.867 --> 00:23:54.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘into the hands of sinners.

00:23:54.078 --> 00:23:56.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Get up, let us go.

00:23:56.831 --> 00:24:00.835 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Look! My betrayer has drawn near.’

00:24:02.336 --> 00:24:04.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
“While he was still speaking,

00:24:04.380 --> 00:24:07.883 line:90% position:50% align:center
“look! Judas, one of the Twelve, came

00:24:07.883 --> 00:24:11.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and with him a large crowd with swords and clubs,

00:24:11.512 --> 00:24:13.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
“sent from the chief priests

00:24:13.514 --> 00:24:15.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and the elders of the people.

00:24:15.891 --> 00:24:20.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Now his betrayer had given them a sign, saying:

00:24:20.187 --> 00:24:24.066 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Whoever it is I kiss, he is the one;

00:24:24.066 --> 00:24:26.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
“take him into custody.’

00:24:26.235 --> 00:24:30.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And going straight up to Jesus, he said:

00:24:30.448 --> 00:24:32.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Greetings, Rabbi!’

00:24:32.575 --> 00:24:36.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and gave him a tender kiss.

00:24:36.203 --> 00:24:37.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But Jesus said to him:

00:24:38.998 --> 00:24:42.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Fellow, for what purpose are you present?’

00:24:44.253 --> 00:24:47.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then they came forward and seized Jesus

00:24:47.173 --> 00:24:49.258 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and took him into custody.

00:24:49.967 --> 00:24:52.428 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But look! one of those with Jesus

00:24:52.428 --> 00:24:55.139 line:90% position:50% align:center
“reached out his hand and drew his sword

00:24:55.139 --> 00:24:57.224 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and struck the slave of the high priest,

00:24:57.224 --> 00:24:59.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
“taking off his ear.

00:24:59.477 --> 00:25:02.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then Jesus said to him:

00:25:02.063 --> 00:25:05.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Return your sword to its place,

00:25:05.149 --> 00:25:07.860 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘for all those who take up the sword

00:25:07.860 --> 00:25:09.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘will perish by the sword.

00:25:10.696 --> 00:25:13.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Or do you think that I cannot appeal to my Father

00:25:13.574 --> 00:25:15.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘to supply me at this moment

00:25:15.576 --> 00:25:17.995 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘more than 12 legions of angels?

00:25:17.995 --> 00:25:19.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘In that case,

00:25:19.997 --> 00:25:22.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘how would the Scriptures be fulfilled

00:25:22.083 --> 00:25:24.835 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that say it must take place this way?’

00:25:26.295 --> 00:25:29.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
“In that hour Jesus said to the crowds:

00:25:29.048 --> 00:25:31.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Did you come out to arrest me

00:25:31.050 --> 00:25:34.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘with swords and clubs as against a robber?

00:25:34.512 --> 00:25:38.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Day after day I used to sit in the temple teaching,

00:25:38.057 --> 00:25:41.394 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘and yet you did not take me into custody.

00:25:41.394 --> 00:25:44.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘But all of this has taken place

00:25:44.021 --> 00:25:46.816 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for the writings of the prophets to be fulfilled.’

00:25:47.858 --> 00:25:52.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then all the disciples abandoned him and fled.”

00:25:55.825 --> 00:25:59.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
Those were significant verses leading up

00:25:59.412 --> 00:26:03.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the two greatest acts of love of all time.

00:26:03.124 --> 00:26:07.837 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah and Jesus cooperated together to undo

00:26:07.837 --> 00:26:10.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
the works of the Devil that were initiated

00:26:10.756 --> 00:26:14.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
back in the garden of Eden with Adam and Eve.

00:26:16.303 --> 00:26:19.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
Whether of the anointed
or of the other sheep,

00:26:19.932 --> 00:26:24.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
we all have the marvelous hope
of everlasting life

00:26:24.228 --> 00:26:27.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
based on the ransom sacrifice

00:26:27.231 --> 00:26:30.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the perfect man Jesus.

00:26:31.944 --> 00:26:34.822 line:90% position:50% align:center
We hope all of you enjoy your evening

00:26:34.822 --> 00:26:37.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
commemorating Jesus’ death

00:26:37.533 --> 00:26:40.077 line:90% position:50% align:center
in behalf of all of us!

